  "prompt": "Is there any Part time universities in Hamburg where we can pursue MS?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several universities in Hamburg that offer part-time Master's programs (MS) suitable for working professionals. Here are a few options you might consider:\n\n1. **Hamburg University of Technology (TUHH)**: TUHH offers various Master's programs, some of which may be available in a part-time format, especially those geared towards professionals.\n\n2. **University of Hamburg**: While many programs are full-time, the University of Hamburg also has some Master's programs that may offer flexible schedules or part-time options, particularly in areas like Business Administration and Education.\n\n3. **Hamburg University of Applied Sciences (HAW Hamburg)**: HAW offers several Master's programs, some of which are designed for part-time study. This is particularly common in fields like Engineering, Business, and Health.\n\n4. **Jacobs University Bremen**: Although not located directly in Hamburg, Jacobs University offers part-time Master's programs and is accessible for commuting.\n\n5. **Private Institutions**: There are also private universities and institutions in Hamburg that may offer part-time MS programs, particularly in business and management.\n\nWhen considering a part-time program, it\u2019s important to check the specific requirements and availability, as well as how the format fits with your work schedule. Always reach out to the admissions offices of the universities for the most accurate and updated information regarding part-time study options.",
